      "date": "2014-04-27 06:56:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nNote that OBD_IOC_CREATE is only used by Lustre testing tools (lctl and loadgen and maybe mds_survey) that build and ship as part of Lustre itself, so there shouldn't be any problem to change the specification of this ioctl. Even better, it should be given a proper IOC number that is using the \"size\" parameter correctly to determine the argument size, which would be a benefit because it would distinguish the new IOC number from the old one so that new tools and old kernels (and vice versa) do not get confused.\n\nThat said, I don't know that anyone has used the ability to create striped files via lctl/OBD_IOC_CREATE in a long time, so maybe there is no loss to remove this complexity entirely?  If that is needed, then it could easily pass lov_mds_md_v[13] instead?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
